Subject: Re: [VB] Emergency light switch and knob on a 66 bus

On Mon, 15 Jul 2002 9:38:24, <paul_f(-at-)ntlworld.com> wrote:

<<So does a 66 switch look like a 67 one, ie the knob flashes?  If not
how do
you know that the lights are flashing?>>

The '67 switch knob has the flashing light built in.  It's a black
rubber knob with a red plastic insert.

The '66 is apparently a red plastic knob (per the photos previously
posted) and I believe there's a red flashing light on the left side of
the speedo that flashes.

-Jim Bryant


